      • withProfiles

        public DockerBuilder withProfiles​(Profile... profiles)
        Build the Docker client with the specified profiles. If withJSONPath(String) has been called, any previously added profiles will be cleared. By default, if withProfiles isn't called and withJSONPath isn't either, a client is constructed with o profiles and can be added to afterwards. However, if withJSONPath is called, it takes priority over profiles
        Parameters:
        profiles - the profiles to add
        Returns:
        this instance for chaining

      • withJSONPath

        public DockerBuilder withJSONPath​(java.lang.String jsonPath)
        Build the Docker client with a path to a JSON configuration file. See profiles.json for an example. The shell variable should be retrieved from here. JSON is the most configurable option If withProfiles(Profile...) is called, any previously set filename is set to an empty string
        Parameters:
        jsonPath - the path to the JSON file
        Returns:
        this instance for chaining
